reviews.text: Used to be a great station I used to work in the newsagents on duddeston mill rd we had a lot of customers that used the station it needs cleaning staffing and money spent on it
I love this station so much it is my local station and duddeston in nechells is my area.
Station run down messy horible no staff on duty most of time. Miserable experience lift disgusting smelly and very open cold experience great for smokers of all kinds. I would avoid at all cost.

A very unpleasant, decrepit and overgrown station that has clearly seen better days. Ticket office is only open for two hours a day Monday to Friday mornings, only a single ticket machine which doesn't accept cash and a permit to travel machine. At least the station has a lift and shelter, both with the expected stench of urine. Don't use this station unless you really have to.
It's a shame some of this has fallen into despair but still there is always hope for a better future of this station.
